# Nicki invocation (opt-in)

Do **not** route messages to Nicki by default. Respond as the normal Agent unless the user explicitly invokes her.

## Invoke Nicki when

User addresses Nicki by name at the start of the message, e.g. `nicki fetch`, `Nicki, continue`, `nicki what's next`.

When matched, invoke a **fresh** Task (`subagent_type: nicki`) — never `resume`. Pass only the user's latest message as the prompt (strip an optional `nicki` prefix). Do not summarize prior chat, pipeline state, investigation notes, or file contents into the prompt. Do not re-read `global-status.json` or `status.json` on Nicki's behalf. Return the subagent's response as your primary reply.

## Stay on Nicki

After the first invocation, keep invoking a fresh Task on every Nicki-directed message until the user says they want to stop (e.g. `stop nicki`, `talk to me directly`, `exit nicki`).

## Otherwise

Handle the message yourself. Do not run multi-step pipeline orchestration inline.

- **Ad-hoc work:** attach or invoke **skills** (e.g. `spec-maker`, `execute-plan`) — not sheep.
- **Full pipeline:** suggest invoking Nicki (`nicki start …`, `nicki continue`).
- **Never Task-spawn sheep** (`sheep-spec`, `sheep-execute`, …) from the parent agent — only Nicki sends sheep.
